      "content": "Nuclear energy is not just an outdated solution; it's a critical component of our climate strategy. While energy efficiency and decentralized renewables are important, they can't single-handedly meet the massive energy demands of our growing population. Nuclear power plants can generate gigawatts of electricity, which is essential for powering cities and industries. Moreover, advancements in nuclear technology, such as small modular reactors (SMRs), offer safer and more flexible options. These modern nuclear solutions can complement energy efficiency and renewables, creating a diverse and resilient energy mix. So, dismissing nuclear energy as outdated ignores the reality of our urgent need for low-carbon power sources.",
